snippet.textDisplay:
-Its actually probably better to rely on guns. If the zombie plague can be transferred by contact, the last thing you want to do is be in splatter distance when you crush their head like a grape. The sound thing is a definitely an issue, but take your pick: a) attract zombies or b) play zombie-virus pinata.
If you need to go for a weapon, go for one with a long reach. Depending on whether zombies are affected by blood loss or not, you should either use a spear and go for the jugular or use a hammer and crush the skull like a walnut. There isn't as much blood vessels in the brain, but try not to get the gray matter on you. (Fun fact, due to the blood-brain barrier, infections are rarely transmittable to the brain. So the brain goo will be considerably safer than blood-goo)



-If cutting off the limb can work, then just disinfect the wound. If you think that won't be effective then use fucking acid. Sure you'll melt of a ton of you arm, but atleast there will be enough muscle to move your trigger finger. And...other things.

-EXTRA NOTES: If the zombie plague were a bio-weapon, It would most likely be spread across an entire area like a nuke ,and the military would quarantine the zone incredibly fast. So either you are in the safe-zone outside of the quarantine area, or you are a zombie.
Sorry to ruin your Zombie survival fantasies.

Ah, but if it were a slow acting zombie virus, one that would gestate for weeks, then it would probable be released during tourist season and naturally spread across the country by travelling tourists.
In that case its likely that, as home staying Hikikomoris that we are, we would probably be the only ones not effected by the zombie virus.
...Althought in that case it would probably be communicable like cold or flu, which would mean the means of transmission isn't just biting.
So make like Tabbes and have a Gas mask handy!
